    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.21.16-17_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">16</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">RALPH F. WOLF
                        <lb/>
                    BOX 509, R. D. 4
                        <lb/>
                    AKRON 1, OHIO</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>June 4, 1946.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>My wife and I have just finished re-reading "The Song of the Indian Wars" as we do every spring.</p>
                
                <p>I wish that I could describe adequately the pleasure that your poetry gives us.</p>
                
                <p>It is difficult for a reader to convey his thanks to an author whom he greatly admires and consequently it is too infrequently done. However,
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.21.16-17_0002"/>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">17</fw>
                    
                    we feel so greatly indebted to you that we want to voice our appreciation even though we do so in most inadequate fashion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours sincerely,</salute>
                    <signed>Ralph F. Wolf</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
